cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.MA 

This paper involves deep learning for real-time localization of surgical tools in the lung using camera images and simulated images. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV), followed by robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also involves training the model using simulated images, which falls under machine learning (cs.LG) and possibly multi-agent systems (cs.MA) since the model can enable closed-loop control by autonomous agents.
